<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="149" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[143,759,241,477]" pageId="14" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis box="[143,262,241,262]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="149">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[378,473,241,263]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[586,680,241,262]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
; body broad, 2.0¥ longer than wide; body coarsely and rugosely punctured; pronotum slightly transverse, 1.5¥ wider than long, widest behind middle, nearly as wide at base; elytra with rugose ridges, very coarsely punctured both between and on top of ridges, some punctures anastomosing; dorsal tooth on right mandible present, moderately well developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[143,638,501,523]" box="[143,638,501,523]" pageId="14" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis box="[143,289,501,522]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="149">Distribution:</emphasis>
Marchena and Pinta Islands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[143,759,547,692]" pageId="14" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis box="[143,268,548,569]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="149">Bionomics:</emphasis>
The species occurs from the littoral and arid zone from sea level up to transition zone forest at 
<quantity box="[143,213,609,630]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="149" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
elevation, and is found in litter under shrubs and in forests. Adults have been collected in February, March and September. Examined: 
<specimenCount box="[542,713,670,692]" pageId="14" pageNumber="149" type="generic">176 specimens</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
